@flint v0 hybrid
@cb[
μ1=auth_middleware;
ρ=skew_30s;
τ=401_refresh_loop;
κ1=backcompat;
κ2=no_widen_skew
]

G: fix(μ1.expiry_cmp)
C: κ1 ∧ κ2 ∧ minimal_diff
H: "expMs < nowMs" ∧ no_skew ⇒ τ @ boundary
P: encode(ρ) → Δ("expMs + skew_ms <= nowMs ⇒ 401") → single_site(μ1)
V: test(exact_boundary_pass) ∧ test(just_over_skew_fail) ∧ test(missing_token_401) ∧ test(malformed_payload_401) ∧ test(unit_ms_mismatch)
R: ! refresh_logic_divergence ∧ ! skew_widening_drift
Q: refresh_path_uses_same_cmp ?
A: Δ(μ1): reject iff "nowMs - expMs > skew_ms"; reuse single cmp helper; add 5 boundary tests

[AUDIT]
bug: strict "<" at exact expiry triggers τ when refresh path tolerates skew.
fix: one helper in μ1, reject only when drift exceeds ρ=30s, applied at single cmp site.
preserve: next(err) path, κ1, no skew widening.
verify: boundary pass at expMs==nowMs-30000, fail at 30001, plus missing/malformed/un
